ategoryTheory.ShortComplex.QuasiIso\">QuasiIso</a> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.mk\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S₁</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.X₁\">X₁</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S₁</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.X₂\">X₂</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">X₃</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S₂</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.X₂\">X₂</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">f</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S₁</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.f\">f</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">g</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.Hom.τ₂\">τ₂</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">zero</span> := <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.mk\">}</a>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.Exact\">Exact</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Epi\">Epi</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.Hom.τ₂\">τ₂</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a morphism of short complexes `φ : S₁ ⟶ S₂` in an abelian category, if `S₁.g = 0`\n(e.g when `S₁` is of the form `S₁.X₁ ⟶ S₁.X₂ ⟶ 0`) and both `S₂.f` and `S₂.g` are zero\n(e.g when `S₂` is of the form `0 ⟶ S₂.X₂ ⟶ 0`), then `φ` is a quasi-isomorphism iff\nthe obvious short complex `S₁.X₁ ⟶ S₁.X₂ ⟶ S₂.X₂` is exact and `φ.τ₂` is an epi. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.quasiIso_iff_of_zeros'","kind":"theorem","line":893,"name":"CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.quasiIso_iff_of_zeros'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.lean#L893-L912"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex.quasiIso_iff_of_zeros\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">ShortComplex</span>.<span class=\"name\">quasiIso_iff_of_zeros</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v_1, u_1}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Abelian/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Abelian\">Abelian</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">S₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">S₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ShortComplex\">ShortComplex</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <span class=\"fn\">S₁</s